This implementation uses the GNU Scientific Library (GSL), available at
http://www.gnu.org/software/gsl/
and available through most modern package managers, e.g. by typing
<on Ubuntu>             sudo apt-get install libgsl0-dev
<on Redhat>             sudo apt-get install libgsl-devel
<on MacOSX with Fink>   fink install gsl
<on Windows using Cygwin> with the Cygwin setup, install 
        libs->gsl-devel
    

Once GSL is installed, and the tarball has been extracted, do a 
   make
to create the binary executable, or 
   make check
to create the binary executable and test it with data from the
Hipparcos Epoch Photometry catalog
(ESA, 1997, The Hipparcos and Tycho Catalogues, ESA SP-1200
http://astro.estec.esa.nl/Hipparcos/CATALOGUE_VOL1/catalog_vol1.html
http://vizier.u-strasbg.fr/viz-bin/ftp-index?/ftp/cats/I/239/epophot  )

Copy the executable 'runchi2' to the appropriate bin directory, if desired

For details on running the program, see the README file.
